{#
  sentinel/templates/base_playbook.md.j2
  ========================================
  Base Markdown playbook template for PhantomNet Sentinel.

  All 7 standard sections:
    1. Header         – title, severity, classification, generation timestamp
    2. Summary        – campaign overview, trigger context, affected assets
    3. IOC Table      – source IPs, ports, protocols, threat intel hits
    4. ATT&CK Mapping – MITRE technique IDs, names, tactics, and descriptions
    5. Containment    – ordered, actionable response checklist
    6. Artifacts      – detection rule references, log sources, evidence paths
    7. Appendix       – context metadata, rollback notes, escalation contacts

  Jinja2 template inheritance support:
    Exposes named {% block %} regions so child templates can override
    individual sections without rewriting the whole document.

  Required context variables
  --------------------------
  title          (str)  – Playbook title
  severity       (str)  – CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW
  attack_pattern (str)  – Normalised attack pattern key
  generated_at   (str)  – ISO-8601 timestamp of generation
#}

